<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1952573-i-dont-understand-why-the-author-would">i dont understand why the author would name a male character ROMA when roma is feminine ? ( and it&#39;s also not a person&#39;s name). If the author sees this i would love an explanation for the name choice.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1952573'><a id="like_count_community_question_1952573" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1952573?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">5 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F50892212-these-violent-delights">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1952573-i-dont-understand-why-the-author-would">9 months ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1952573-i-dont-understand-why-the-author-would">See all 8 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
