<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/93632861-chloe-gong"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1564479307i/93632861._UY100_CR1,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/93632861-chloe-gong">Chloe Gong</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Someone directed me over here to answer (I don&apos;t usually see Goodreads questions, any other ones should be sent direct to me) but yes, I do have one! <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Someone directed me over here to answer (I don't usually see Goodreads questions, any other ones should be sent direct to me) but yes, I do have one! Roma is masculine in Slavic cultures, you might referring to different cultures. It's a diminutive for Roman, which is indeed a very Russian name. Hope that helps!<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
