</u>!!<br/><br/>Overall: this book was a 2.5-star read for me. <br/><br/>It certainly had elements that were interesting but ultimately was lackluster when it came to execution. <br/><br/>The science felt...awful...simply awful and neither of the characters felt particularly compelling to read about...I probably won&apos;t be continuing this series cause I simply cannot care enough to continue. For more details, check out my video review!<br/><br/><a href='http://bit.ly/33ii2CT' rel='nofollow noopener'>YouTube</a> | <a href='http://www.mirandareads.com' rel='nofollow noopener'>Blog</a> | <a href='https://www.instagram.com/miranda_reads/?hl=en' rel='nofollow noopener'>Instagram</a> |</span>
  <span id="freeText2081779568630280276" style="display:none"><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1608654398i/30572216._SX540_.jpg" width="400" height="225" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Just posted my <u>
