        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3790089571" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6643613997552931722"><b>“The stars incline us, they do not bind us.”</b><br/><br/>Buddy read with <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/108084810-em-iforgotsalt' rel='nofollow noopener'>Em</a>💖<br/><br/>⭐⭐⭐⭐ stars<br/><br/><br/>These Violent Delights is a Romeo Juliet retelling. But I tell you it&apos;s soo much more than that.<br/>Power struggle, inner conflict and forbidden romance or something like that<br/>aka the ALMOST perfect book&lt;3<br/>I felt something was lacking in this book<br/>*shooketh*<br/>I will detail it below!<br/><br/><b>Plot</b><br/><br/>Juliette is the heir of the Scarlet gang. Roma is the heir of the White flowers.<br/>There was once a time when both were in love. But it&apos;s not the same a</span>
  <span id="freeText6643613997552931722" style="display:none"><b>“The stars incline us, they do not bind us.”</b><br><br>Buddy read with <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/108084810-em-iforgotsalt" rel="nofollow noopener">Em</a>💖<br><br>⭐⭐⭐⭐ stars<br><br><br>These Violent Delights is a Romeo Juliet retelling. But I tell you it's soo much more than that.<br>Power struggle, inner conflict and forbidden romance or something like that<br>aka the ALMOST perfect book&lt;3<br>I felt something was lacking in this book<br>*shooketh*<br>I will detail it below!<br><br><b>Plot</b><br><br>Juliette is the heir of the Scarlet gang. Roma is the heir of the White flowers.<br>There was once a time when both were in love. But it's not the same anymore. Scared with betrayal, they will now do anything to take control.<br>But the gangs are not the only superpowers here. The foreigners are aiming to take control of Shangai. Now Roma and Juliette has to protect their city from them while simultaneously fighting against a dark force that has vowed to kill the entire city.<br>Together they have to stop it. But will it work? Or will their anger take advantage of them?<br><br><br><b>Writing</b><br><br>Wow the writing was absolutely beautiful<br>Chloe gong has blown me away<br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1621485927ra/31358332.gif" width="350" height="250" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><i>“Memories were beastly little creatures, after all—they rose with the faintest whiff of nourishment.”</i><br><br>Ugh omg everytime I finish reading I delete the copy from my kindle before I write my review and all my notes go poof<br>*bangs head against wall bcz I'm stupid*<br><br>Anyways I can tell you that I very much adored the writing of TVD&lt;3 It was magical and that type of suspense can only be built if there is good writing&lt;3<br><br><br><b>World</b><br><br>OKAY WOW I majorly stan the world here. 1920 Shangai, um sign me up!<br>I think the author's asian roots are the reason why the world is soo good and accurate. She has done her research unlike some *cough**cough*<br><br>it was soo fun to read and it was my fav part of the book&lt;3<br><br><br><b>Characters</b><br><br><b>Juliette</b><br><br><i>“Even the land of dreams needs to wake up sometimes.”</i><br><br>Why do I love Juliette soo much? Why do I care for her?<br>BECAUSE SHE IS PERFECT<br><br>Sure, she's a little extra and does a lot of drama but she a sweetheart.<br>She is very brave and very clever. You will always hope that she will fight with u and not against u because then u will be dead. <br><br>She is constantly troubled by her identity, to where she belongs. She was born Chinese by birth but she spent almost her entire life in America. She finds it hard in Shangai because most exclude her for her identity<br><br><i>Juliette breathed in and found her lungs to be horribly tight. Could she never be both? Was she doomed to choose one country or the other? Be an American or nothing?</i><br><br>Well I don't care if she is American or Chinese because I will ALWAYS love her<br><br><s>me wondering why I have soo many book bf and gf</s><br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1585272041ra/29176826.gif" width="350" height="250" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><br><b>Roma</b><br><br>While Juliette is the definition of Perfection with a capital P, Roma is polar opposite<br>Roma = BORING<br><br>I actually don't care about him. There is nothing about him that stood out me :(<br>AND that was extremely disappointing<br><br>The male MC was supposed to make me swoon, but nothing ahh..... I wished at least we could explore more of Roma's Russian roots, but we don't get that either.<br><br>No opinion about him<br>*melts into the background*<br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1443859067ra/16422882.gif" width="350" height="250" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><br><b>Kathleen</b> is another character who is PERFECT. I love her. She is shy and clever and brave&lt;3 <br>Me and Em were fangirling over her the entire time ^_^<br><br><b>Roslaind</b>, that sassy queen. She is actually very straightforward. She wont hesitate to punch u if u wrong her heeee<br><br><b>Marshall</b> why is he soo good&lt;3 I loved him and omg he is perfect. He is like the imaginary best friend who listens to all of our grievances while consoling us 😪<br><br><b>Benedickt</b> is cute ugh. I honestly have no idea why he hangs out with Roma. Ben is awesome!<br><br>Basically you should know that All of the side characters and Juliette are sooo much better than Roma......................<br><br><br><b>Romance</b><br><br><i>“You destroy me and then you kiss me. You give me a reason to hat you and then you give me a reason to love you. Is this a lie or the truth? Is the a ploy or your heart reaching for me?”</i><br><br>Juliette you honestly deserve better. Roma is an idiot :(<br>But ig they are kinda cute?<br><br>I wish there was more focus on Roma an Juliette so as to build the romnce and make us root for the ship. But there wasn't enough, and now I don't ship them HARD.<br>Can Juliette find someone better?<br>Pretty Please?<br>Rosalind mayb?<br><br>I know it will never happen...<br><br>But anyways If they both end up together in the next book, I don't have a problem. If the author builds more on it the sequel, then u can see me SHIPPING HARD<br><br>BUT FOR NOW : <br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1493728189ra/22645856.gif" width="350" height="250" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>*melts into the background again*<br><br><b>Final thoughts</b><br><br>SO the ending destroyed me. Im ded, I'm writing this as a ghost<br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1523192971ra/25344155.gif" width="350" height="250" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>I loved the whole story, the concept of that mysterious insect, typical asian parents (i can relate) everything was awesome.<br>UGH I CNAT WAIT TO READ TEH NEXT ONEEE<br><br><b>Places it lacked </b><br><br>*ROMA - the male lead could have been better<br>*The romance would have been better if there was a bit more build up. After all this is a Romeo Juliet retelling<br><br><br>That is all, otherwise perfection. I loved her writing!!!<br><br>Does it deserve the hype? A BIT<br>Will I reccomned it ? YES<br>Re Read? Mayb closer to the sequel's release date!<br><br>This is my review<br>Thank you<br>*bows*<br><br><br>|<a href="https://booksandbrownies820513218.wordpress.com/" rel="nofollow noopener">Blog|</a><a href="https://www.pinterest.ca/reader_nash/_saved/" rel="nofollow noopener">Pintrest</a>|<br><br>--------------------<br><br><i>My rating system:<br>5⭐ - I loved it soo much! New favorite<br>4⭐ - It was really good! But something was missing<br>3⭐ - It was nice..but had more potential<br>2⭐ - I did not like it at all!... It could have been soo much better<br>1⭐ - Nope. Just No. I hate it</i></span>
  <a data-text-id="6643613997552931722" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

