<div id="review_3470513243" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3470513243" />
    <a title="❦ jazmin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/70652463-jazmin"><img alt="❦ jazmin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1622323635p2/70652463.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3470513243?book_show_action=true">Apr 19, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="❦ jazmin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="❦ jazmin" href="/user/show/70652463-jazmin">❦ jazmin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/70652463-jazmin?shelf=2021">2021</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/70652463-jazmin?shelf=best-or-longest-reviews-ive-written">best-or-longest-reviews-ive-written</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/70652463-jazmin?shelf=genre-retelling">genre-retelling</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/70652463-jazmin?shelf=genre-romance">genre-romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/70652463-jazmin?shelf=representation-lgbtqia">representation-lgbtqia</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/70652463-jazmin?shelf=genre-fantasy">genre-fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/70652463-jazmin?shelf=genre-historical">genre-historical</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/70652463-jazmin?shelf=genre-mafia-or-gang">genre-mafia-or-gang</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/70652463-jazmin?shelf=representation-strong-women">representation-strong-women</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/70652463-jazmin?shelf=trope-rivals-to-lovers-or-bully">trope-rivals-to-lovers-or-bully</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3470513243" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14769023431961699597"><blockquote>
  <b>“The stars incline us, they do not bind us.”</b>
</blockquote><br/><br/>I know, I know, I’m super late to the party. But this is a Romeo and Juliet retelling and I hate the death trope. I think it’s easy to put two and two together. However, I’m incredibly glad that I finally picked up this book because it was phenomenal. I’m so invested in these characters now and I can’t wait for Our Violent Ends. <br/><br/><b>
  <u>⇢The Plot</u>
</b><br/>I’ve never read Romeo and Juliet in its entirety (I got bored) so I can’t say how closely or loosely based o</span>
  <span id="freeText14769023431961699597" style="display:none"><blockquote>
  <b>“The stars incline us, they do not bind us.”</b>
</blockquote><br /><br />I know, I know, I’m super late to the party. But this is a Romeo and Juliet retelling and I hate the death trope. I think it’s easy to put two and two together. However, I’m incredibly glad that I finally picked up this book because it was phenomenal. I’m so invested in these characters now and I can’t wait for Our Violent Ends. <br /><br /><b>
  <u>⇢The Plot</u>
</b><br />I’ve never read Romeo and Juliet in its entirety (I got bored) so I can’t say how closely or loosely based on it this book was, but I don’t think it was too similar because there were a lot of fantasy elements, which I really liked. Also, something that sets this book apart from other retellings for me is the sheer amount of time and effort put into researching the different cultures and historical facts, and those definitely weren’t in the original play. I absolutely loved how much we got to see of Chinese culture in the past, and Russian culture too. <br /><br />As for the fantasy parts, I thought they were really well done. You know a book is good when you can feel like you’re inside the story even if it’s not something that exists in real life, and I definitely felt that here. Every time the insects were mentioned I felt like they were crawling on me *cries*<br /><br />The only thing I felt I didn’t love was that we didn’t get flashbacks to the past. A lot of interactions that took place three(?) years earlier between Roma and Juliette were referenced but never explained in detail and maybe this is an unpopular opinion but I love flashbacks because I feel like I can understand the characters more. Not really something that would impact my rating of the book but just a comment! <br /><br /><b>
  <u>⇢Juliette and Roma</u>
</b><br /> I am obsessed with these two. I think I’ve said those words a billion times over the course of reading this book because I. am. obsessed. Not only with them as a couple, but as their own characters. Once again, I haven’t read Romeo and Juliet, but I am entirely convinced that Romeo and Juliet have nothing on Roma and Juliette. Juliette was such a fun main character and lived up to the expectations I had for her based on all the things I had heard. <br /><br /><blockquote>
  <i>“I was raised in hatred, Roma. I could never be your lover, only your killer.”</i>
</blockquote><br /><br />I also loved Roma, because I am obsessed with characters who don’t necessarily agree with the rules or expectations they were brought up with. He was also just such a complex character that you want to know more! <br /><br />Obviously, I also loved their romance, but at times I felt like their relationship was progressing suddenly and then going backwards. Not to be repetitive but that’s another reason why I wanted the flashbacks! Their relationship would have felt more natural. <br /><br /><blockquote>
  <i>“Wasn't playing with her heart once enough? Hadn't he already torn her into two and left her to the wolves once before?”</i>
</blockquote><br /><br /><b>
  <u>⇢Other Characters</u>
</b><br />The best books have good side characters, and These Violent Delights is definitely under that category because I adored Benedikt, Marshall and Kathleen. I can’t wait for more of BenMars, and I’m so excited to see more of Kathleen! Also, I hate Tyler. Just wanted to add that in :)<br /><br /><blockquote>
  <i>“Sometimes it was hard for Kathleen to remember that she was still her own person, not just shards of a mirror, reflecting back a thousand different personalities most fitting for the situation.”</i>
</blockquote><br /><br /><blockquote>. ⋅ ˚̣- : ✧ : – ⭒ ❦ ⭒ – : ✧ : -˚̣⋅ .</blockquote> <br /><br /><a href="http://open.spotify.com/user/jazmania5353" rel="nofollow noopener">MY SPOTIFY ❦</a><br /><br /><a href="https://linktr.ee/jazminnjones" rel="nofollow noopener">MY LINKTREE ❦</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="14769023431961699597" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

