<div id="review_3652698781" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3652698781" />
    <a title="krista ☽✧" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/72478075-krista"><img alt="krista ☽✧" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1626102224p2/72478075.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3652698781?book_show_action=true">Jan 19, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="krista ☽✧" class="user" itemprop="url" name="krista ☽✧" href="/user/show/72478075-krista">krista ☽✧</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/72478075-krista?shelf=enemies-too-lovers">enemies-too-lovers</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3652698781" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4434405313123694521"><b> “Memories were beastly little creatures, after all—they rose with the faintest whiff of nourishment.” </b> <br/><br/>unpopular opinion alert , dont kill me people. i expected this too blow my mind away but it didnt. iIt was just a like. which is not bad but not super good like i thought it would be so yeah. * little dissapointed noises *<br/><br/><b>These violent delights </b> is the debut novel by Chloe Gong. The story focusses on two gangs that both live and want to rule Shanghai in 1926. We have Juliette Cai who is the he</span>
  <span id="freeText4434405313123694521" style="display:none"><b> “Memories were beastly little creatures, after all—they rose with the faintest whiff of nourishment.” </b> <br /><br />unpopular opinion alert , dont kill me people. i expected this too blow my mind away but it didnt. iIt was just a like. which is not bad but not super good like i thought it would be so yeah. * little dissapointed noises *<br /><br /><b>These violent delights </b> is the debut novel by Chloe Gong. The story focusses on two gangs that both live and want to rule Shanghai in 1926. We have Juliette Cai who is the heir of the scarlet gang the current ruler of shanghai who wants to do anything to protect her gang. And we have Roma Montagov who is the heir of the other gang in shanghai ; the white flowers. These gangs are enemies of each other. Juliette and Roma once had a romantic forbidden relationship bus trough betrayel this was destroyed. But once the people of both gangs start rippin their own throat out because of a mysterious disease which may be caused by a monster both heirs have to work together again to explore the truth behind these mysterious suicides and the monster. I raded this is a retelling from Romaeo and Juliette which I never read so I don’t really have to say anything about that or if it is done well oops. <br /><br />I felt like this book is definitely really focused on the plot of the book and about the events that are happening and finding out more about this monster and the politics in the world of the two gangs. I really enjoyed the plot and I always love mysterious plots where things happen and we have to find out what these things are with the charracters. I liked the horror that came with it because well Krizzie likes horror and gross details. But I did expect this to be more character and romance focused then it was. At least for me it felt more plot focused. I personally couldn’t really connect to the charracters as I like to have in a story. I feel like they wherent explored in depth enough maybe. I just felt like I needed more of them and more in their depth if that makes sense. I do feel like Juliette is a interesting morally grey ish main character that has more side’s to her. Because I could not connect to the charracters as much as I wanted to I also did not connect to the romance as I wanted too. I also feel like the romance definitely isn’t here much , it felt a little too less for my taste and I did not really feel much with it because there just wasn’t much. I did like the romance as it developed more towards the ending. I did really enjoy the plot twistst in the end of the book and HA Lia warned me and yes there is a cliffhanger in here and I need information , now ?! <br />There is also a hint of a LGTB + rep in this book between Marshall and Benedikt which I am here for. <br /><br />This book also deals with a lot of history of the reality of this time period. There is white colonization in here which was done well and made me think you see how the white culture want to steal shanghai , this country away and make it their own and let the culture and people of the land disappear. Which is disgusting. <br /><br />Overall i thought i would totally love this book and that did not happen. I enjoyed it but it did not blow me away. I enjoyed the plot and i liked the charracters but i didnt felt really connected to them and feel like i need more. Also the romance was less focus in the story , it is more a plot based book. and i also couldnt really connect to the romance as i wanted too because it felt too less for me. Enjoyable book but it didnt blow krizzie away as she expected too.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4434405313123694521" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

